post_text:
The 2020 WHS Outstanding Speech and Theatre Senior.

This young woman had been involved with the Speech and Theatre departments since she was in Junior High. In high school she excelled in both departments and as the years progressed she became a leader and mentor to the other students. She has lettered all 4 years on the Speech Team and collected many competition medals and honors. This year she was again recognized, as exceptional, by the Kaysinger Coaches with 1st Team All Conference Speech Team Honors.

She has maintained vital on stage and back stage roles in all Theatre productions in her junior high and high school years. This year she performed both as a lead character and as Senior Editor for the student written all school spring play.

The WHS Outstanding Senior Speech & Theatre Senior is JOANNA BRANT!

(Previously MED492 - The Independent Film Study Course)

Pitch Session: October 23rd, 12:30 - 2:00 p.m. in Craig 319

You will need:
- A Completed Script
- A clear, concise, well written synopsis
- A crew list (of at least department heads)
- A cast list (if known)
- Equipment list (and reasons for use)
- Shooting Schedule
- Budget
- Look book
- Preferred faculty advisor(s)
- A solid pitch
For more information, check out the https://www.facebook.com/AMPG.MSU or contact our MJF faculty!
